==English==
===Etymology===
Back formation from [[pro bono]]
===Adjective===
'''low bono'''
#{{law}} (''US, of legal work'') at a [[discounted]] [[rate]], especially to [[under]]-[[represented]] [[communities]]
===References===
*"Solos, Small Firms Team Up to Support 'Low Bono' Legal Work" Small Firm Business 03-31-2005 [http://www.law.com/jsp/lawArticleSFB.jsp?id=1112177107389].
====usage notes====
*Sometimes "low bono" appears to be used as an adverb, as in the sentence "I was working this case low bono." or "I am working low bono;" but this is probably a shortening of "working on a low bono basis," rather than a truly adverbial use.